{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"This is me. My name is Ben Saunders."},{"time":2000,"text":"I specialize in dragging heavy things"},{"time":4000,"text":"around cold places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":6000,"text":"On May 11th last year,"},{"time":8000,"text":"I stood alone at the North geographic Pole."},{"time":11000,"text":"I was the only human being in an area"},{"time":13000,"text":"one-and-a-half times the size of America,"},{"time":15000,"text":"five-and-a-half thousand square miles."},{"time":17000,"text":"More than 2,000 people have climbed Everest."},{"time":19000,"text":"12 people have stood on the moon."},{"time":21000,"text":"Including me, only four people"},{"time":23000,"text":"have skied solo to the North Pole."},{"time":26000,"text":"And I think the reason for that --"},{"time":28000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":32000,"text":"-- thank you -- I think the reason for that is that it's -- it's --"},{"time":34000,"text":"well, it's as Chris said, bonkers."},{"time":36000,"text":"It's a journey that is right at the limit"},{"time":39000,"text":"of human capability."},{"time":41000,"text":"I skied the equivalent of 31 marathons"},{"time":43000,"text":"back to back. 800 miles in 10 weeks."},{"time":46000,"text":"And I was dragging all the food I needed,"},{"time":48000,"text":"the supplies, the equipment, sleeping bag,"},{"time":50000,"text":"one change of underwear -- everything I needed for nearly three months."},{"time":53000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":56000,"text":"What we're going to try and do today, in the 16 and a bit minutes I've got left,"},{"time":59000,"text":"is to try and answer three questions. The first one is, why?"},{"time":62000,"text":"The second one is,"},{"time":64000,"text":"how do you go to the loo at minus 40?"},{"time":66000,"text":"\"Ben, I've read somewhere that at minus 40,"},{"time":69000,"text":"exposed skin becomes frostbitten in less than a minute, so how do you answer the call of nature?\""},{"time":72000,"text":"I don't want to answer these now. I'll come on to them at the end."},{"time":75000,"text":"Third one: how do you top that? What's next?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":79000,"text":"It all started back in 2001."},{"time":81000,"text":"My first expedition was with a guy called Pen Hadow -- enormously experienced chap."},{"time":84000,"text":"This was like my polar apprenticeship."},{"time":87000,"text":"We were trying to ski from this group of islands up here,"},{"time":90000,"text":"Severnaya Zemlya, to the North Pole."},{"time":92000,"text":"And the thing that fascinates me about the North Pole,"},{"time":94000,"text":"geographic North Pole, is that it's slap bang in the middle of the sea."},{"time":97000,"text":"This is about as good as maps get,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and to reach it you've got to ski literally"},{"time":101000,"text":"over the frozen crust,"},{"time":103000,"text":"the floating skin of ice on the Artic Ocean."},{"time":106000,"text":"I'd spoken to all the experts."},{"time":108000,"text":"I'd read lots of books. I studied maps and charts."},{"time":110000,"text":"But I realized on the morning of day one"},{"time":112000,"text":"that I had no idea exactly"},{"time":114000,"text":"what I'd let myself in for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"I was 23 years old. No one my age"},{"time":118000,"text":"had attempted anything like this,"},{"time":120000,"text":"and pretty quickly, almost everything"},{"time":122000,"text":"that could have gone wrong did go wrong."},{"time":124000,"text":"We were attacked by a polar bear on day two."},{"time":127000,"text":"I had frostbite in my left big toe."},{"time":130000,"text":"We started running very low on food. We were both pretty hungry, losing lots of weight."},{"time":133000,"text":"Some very unusual weather conditions, very difficult ice conditions."},{"time":137000,"text":"We had"},{"time":139000,"text":"decidedly low-tech communications."},{"time":141000,"text":"We couldn't afford a satellite phone, so we had HF radio."},{"time":144000,"text":"You can see two ski poles sticking out of the roof of the tent."},{"time":146000,"text":"There's a wire dangling down either side."},{"time":148000,"text":"That was our HF radio antenna."},{"time":150000,"text":"We had less than two hours"},{"time":152000,"text":"two-way communication with the outside world in two months."},{"time":156000,"text":"Ultimately, we ran out of time."},{"time":158000,"text":"We'd skied 400 miles. We were just over 200 miles left"},{"time":161000,"text":"to go to the Pole, and we'd run out of time."},{"time":163000,"text":"We were too late into the summer; the ice was starting to melt;"},{"time":165000,"text":"we spoke to the Russian helicopter pilots on the radio,"},{"time":167000,"text":"and they said, \"Look boys, you've run out of time."},{"time":169000,"text":"We've got to pick you up.\""},{"time":171000,"text":"And I felt that I had failed, wholeheartedly."},{"time":174000,"text":"I was a failure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"The one goal, the one dream I'd had"},{"time":178000,"text":"for as long as I could remember -- I hadn't even come close."},{"time":182000,"text":"And skiing along that first trip, I had two"},{"time":184000,"text":"imaginary video clips that I'd replay over and over again in my mind"},{"time":187000,"text":"when the going got tough, just to keep my motivation going."},{"time":190000,"text":"The first one was reaching the Pole itself."},{"time":193000,"text":"I could see vividly, I suppose,"},{"time":195000,"text":"being filmed out of the door of a helicopter, there was, kind of, rock music playing in the background,"},{"time":198000,"text":"and I had a ski pole with a Union Jack, you know, flying in the wind."},{"time":201000,"text":"I could see myself sticking the flag in a pole, you know --"},{"time":204000,"text":"ah, glorious moment -- the music kind of reaching a crescendo."},{"time":206000,"text":"The second video clip"},{"time":208000,"text":"that I imagined was getting back to Heathrow airport,"},{"time":210000,"text":"and I could see again, vividly,"},{"time":212000,"text":"the camera flashbulbs going off,"},{"time":214000,"text":"the paparazzi, the autograph hunters,"},{"time":217000,"text":"the book agents coming to sign me up for a deal."},{"time":219000,"text":"And of course, neither of these things happened."},{"time":222000,"text":"We didn't get to the Pole, and we didn't have any money"},{"time":225000,"text":"to pay anyone to do the PR, so no one had heard"},{"time":227000,"text":"of this expedition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"And I got back to Heathrow. My mum was there; my brother was there;"},{"time":232000,"text":"my granddad was there -- had a little Union Jack --"},{"time":235000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":237000,"text":"-- and that was about it. I went back to live with my mum."},{"time":239000,"text":"I was physically exhausted,"},{"time":241000,"text":"mentally an absolute wreck, considered myself a failure."},{"time":244000,"text":"In a huge amount of debt personally to this expedition,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and lying on my mum's sofa,"},{"time":248000,"text":"day in day out, watching daytime TV."},{"time":252000,"text":"My brother sent me a text message, an SMS --"},{"time":254000,"text":"it was a quote from the \"Simpsons.\" It said,"},{"time":256000,"text":"\"You tried your hardest and failed miserably."},{"time":260000,"text":"The lesson is: don't even try.\""},{"time":262000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":263000,"text":"Fast forward three years. I did eventually get off the sofa,"},{"time":266000,"text":"and start planning another expedition. This time,"},{"time":268000,"text":"I wanted to go right across, on my own this time,"},{"time":270000,"text":"from Russia, at the top of the map,"},{"time":272000,"text":"to the North Pole, where the sort of kink in the middle is,"},{"time":274000,"text":"and then on to Canada."},{"time":276000,"text":"No one has made a complete crossing of the Arctic Ocean on their own."},{"time":279000,"text":"Two Norwegians did it as a team in 2000. No one's done it solo."},{"time":283000,"text":"Very famous, very accomplished Italian mountaineer,"},{"time":287000,"text":"Reinhold Messner, tried it in 1995,"},{"time":288000,"text":"and he was rescued after a week."},{"time":290000,"text":"He described this expedition as 10 times"},{"time":293000,"text":"as dangerous as Everest."},{"time":295000,"text":"So for some reason, this was what I wanted to have a crack at,"},{"time":300000,"text":"but I knew that even to stand a chance of getting home in one piece,"},{"time":302000,"text":"let alone make it across to Canada,"},{"time":304000,"text":"I had to take a radical approach."},{"time":307000,"text":"This meant everything from perfecting the"},{"time":309000,"text":"sawn-off, sub-two-gram toothbrush,"},{"time":312000,"text":"to working with one of the world's leading nutritionists"},{"time":314000,"text":"in developing a completely new,"},{"time":316000,"text":"revolutionary nutritional strategy from scratch:"},{"time":319000,"text":"6,000 calories a day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321000,"text":"And the expedition started in February last year."},{"time":324000,"text":"Big support team. We had a film crew,"},{"time":326000,"text":"a couple of logistics people with us,"},{"time":328000,"text":"my girlfriend, a photographer."},{"time":331000,"text":"At first it was pretty sensible. We flew British Airways to Moscow."},{"time":335000,"text":"The next bit in Siberia to Krasnoyarsk,"},{"time":337000,"text":"on a Russian internal airline called KrasAir,"},{"time":340000,"text":"spelled K-R-A-S."},{"time":342000,"text":"The next bit, we'd chartered a pretty elderly Russian plane"},{"time":345000,"text":"to fly us up to a town called Khatanga,"},{"time":347000,"text":"which was the sort of last bit of civilization."},{"time":350000,"text":"Our cameraman, who it turned out was a pretty nervous flier at the best of times,"},{"time":354000,"text":"actually asked the pilot, before we got on the plane, how long this flight would take,"},{"time":356000,"text":"and the pilot -- Russian pilot -- completely deadpan, replied,"},{"time":359000,"text":"\"Six hours -- if we live.\""},{"time":362000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":365000,"text":"We got to Khatanga."},{"time":367000,"text":"I think the joke is that Khatanga isn't the end of the world,"},{"time":370000,"text":"but you can see it from there."},{"time":372000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":373000,"text":"It was supposed to be an overnight stay. We were stuck there for 10 days."},{"time":376000,"text":"There was a kind of vodka-fueled pay dispute between"},{"time":378000,"text":"the helicopter pilots and the people that owned the helicopter,"},{"time":380000,"text":"so we were stuck. We couldn't move."},{"time":382000,"text":"Finally, morning of day 11, we got the all-clear,"},{"time":385000,"text":"loaded up the helicopters -- two helicopters flying in tandem --"},{"time":389000,"text":"dropped me off at the edge of the pack ice."},{"time":391000,"text":"We had a frantic sort of 45 minutes of filming,"},{"time":394000,"text":"photography; while the helicopter was still there,"},{"time":396000,"text":"I did an interview on the satellite phone;"},{"time":398000,"text":"and then everyone else climbed back into the helicopter,"},{"time":402000,"text":"wham, the door closed, and I was alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407000,"text":"And I don't know if words will ever quite do that moment justice."},{"time":409000,"text":"All I could think about was running back up to the door,"},{"time":411000,"text":"banging on the door, and saying, \"Look guys,"},{"time":413000,"text":"I haven't quite thought this through.\""},{"time":415000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":420000,"text":"To make things worse, you can just see the white dot"},{"time":422000,"text":"up at the top right hand side of the screen; that's a full moon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425000,"text":"Because we'd been held up in Russia, of course,"},{"time":427000,"text":"the full moon brings the highest and lowest tides;"},{"time":429000,"text":"when you're standing on the frozen surface of the sea,"},{"time":432000,"text":"high and low tides generally mean"},{"time":434000,"text":"that interesting things are going to happen -- the ice is going to start moving around a bit."},{"time":438000,"text":"I was, you can see there, pulling two sledges."},{"time":440000,"text":"Grand total in all, 95 days of food and fuel,"},{"time":442000,"text":"180 kilos -- that's almost exactly 400 pounds."},{"time":446000,"text":"When the ice was flat or flattish,"},{"time":448000,"text":"I could just about pull both."},{"time":450000,"text":"When the ice wasn't flat, I didn't have a hope in hell."},{"time":452000,"text":"I had to pull one, leave it, and go back and get the other one."},{"time":454000,"text":"Literally scrambling through what's called pressure ice --"},{"time":457000,"text":"the ice had been smashed up under the pressure of the currents of the ocean,"},{"time":460000,"text":"the wind and the tides."},{"time":463000,"text":"NASA described the ice conditions last year as the worst since records began."},{"time":468000,"text":"And it's always drifting. The pack ice is always drifting."},{"time":471000,"text":"I was skiing into headwinds for nine"},{"time":473000,"text":"out of the 10 weeks I was alone last year,"},{"time":475000,"text":"and I was drifting backwards most of the time."},{"time":478000,"text":"My record was minus 2.5 miles."},{"time":481000,"text":"I got up in the morning, took the tent down, skied north for seven-and-a-half hours,"},{"time":484000,"text":"put the tent up, and I was two and a half miles further back"},{"time":487000,"text":"than when I'd started."},{"time":489000,"text":"I literally couldn't keep up with the drift of the ice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493000,"text":"(Video): So it's day 22."},{"time":498000,"text":"I'm lying in the tent, getting ready to go."},{"time":501000,"text":"The weather is just appalling --"},{"time":503000,"text":"oh, drifted back about five miles"},{"time":506000,"text":"in the last -- last night."},{"time":508000,"text":"Later in the expedition, the problem was no longer the ice."},{"time":511000,"text":"It was a lack of ice -- open water."},{"time":513000,"text":"I knew this was happening. I knew the Artic was warming."},{"time":516000,"text":"I knew there was more open water. And I had a secret weapon up my sleeve."},{"time":519000,"text":"This was my little bit of bio-mimicry."},{"time":521000,"text":"Polar bears on the Artic Ocean move in dead straight lines."},{"time":525000,"text":"If they come to water, they'll climb in, swim across it."},{"time":527000,"text":"So we had a dry suit developed -- I worked with a team in Norway --"},{"time":530000,"text":"based on a sort of survival suit --"},{"time":532000,"text":"I suppose, that helicopter pilots would wear --"},{"time":534000,"text":"that I could climb into. It would go on over my boots, over my mittens,"},{"time":536000,"text":"it would pull up around my face, \nand seal pretty tightly around my face."},{"time":539000,"text":"And this meant I could ski"},{"time":541000,"text":"over very thin ice,"},{"time":543000,"text":"and if I fell through, it wasn't the end of the world."},{"time":545000,"text":"It also meant, if the worst came to the worst,"},{"time":547000,"text":"I could actually jump in and swim across"},{"time":549000,"text":"and drag the sledge over after me."},{"time":552000,"text":"Some pretty radical technology,"},{"time":554000,"text":"a radical approach --but it worked perfectly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556000,"text":"Another exciting thing we did last year"},{"time":558000,"text":"was with communications technology."},{"time":561000,"text":"In 1912, Shackleton's Endurance expedition --"},{"time":564000,"text":"there was -- one of his crew, a guy called Thomas Orde-Lees."},{"time":567000,"text":"He said, \"The explorers of 2012,"},{"time":569000,"text":"if there is anything left to explore,"},{"time":571000,"text":"will no doubt carry pocket wireless telephones"},{"time":574000,"text":"fitted with wireless telescopes.\""},{"time":577000,"text":"Well, Orde-Lees guessed wrong by about eight years. This is my pocket wireless telephone,"},{"time":580000,"text":"Iridium satellite phone."},{"time":582000,"text":"The wireless telescope was a digital camera I had tucked in my pocket."},{"time":585000,"text":"And every single day of the 72 days I was alone on the ice,"},{"time":587000,"text":"I was blogging live from my tent,"},{"time":590000,"text":"sending back a little diary piece,"},{"time":592000,"text":"sending back information on the distance I'd covered --"},{"time":594000,"text":"the ice conditions, the temperature --"},{"time":596000,"text":"and a daily photo."},{"time":598000,"text":"Remember, 2001,"},{"time":600000,"text":"we had less than two hours radio contact with the outside world."},{"time":604000,"text":"Last year, blogging live from an expedition"},{"time":606000,"text":"that's been described as 10 times as dangerous as Everest."},{"time":609000,"text":"It wasn't all high-tech. This is navigating"},{"time":611000,"text":"in what's called a whiteout."},{"time":613000,"text":"When you get lots of mist, low cloud, the wind starts blowing the snow up."},{"time":616000,"text":"You can't see an awful lot. You can just see, there's a yellow"},{"time":618000,"text":"ribbon tied to one of my ski poles."},{"time":620000,"text":"I'd navigate using the direction of the wind."},{"time":622000,"text":"So, kind of a weird combination of high-tech and low-tech."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625000,"text":"I got to the Pole on the 11th of May."},{"time":627000,"text":"It took me 68 days to get there from Russia,"},{"time":629000,"text":"and there is nothing there."},{"time":632000,"text":"(Laughter)."},{"time":634000,"text":"There isn't even a pole at the Pole. There's nothing there,"},{"time":636000,"text":"purely because it's sea ice. It's drifting."},{"time":639000,"text":"Stick a flag there, leave it there, pretty soon it will drift off, usually towards Canada or Greenland."},{"time":642000,"text":"I knew this, but I was expecting something."},{"time":647000,"text":"Strange mixture of feelings: it was extremely warm by this stage,"},{"time":651000,"text":"a lot of open water around, and"},{"time":653000,"text":"of course, elated that I'd got there under my own steam,"},{"time":656000,"text":"but starting to really realize"},{"time":659000,"text":"that my chances of making it all the way across to Canada,"},{"time":661000,"text":"which was still 400 miles away,"},{"time":663000,"text":"were slim at best."},{"time":665000,"text":"The only proof I've got that I was there"},{"time":667000,"text":"is a blurry photo of my GPS, the little satellite navigation gadget."},{"time":670000,"text":"You can just see --"},{"time":672000,"text":"there's a nine and a string of zeros here."},{"time":675000,"text":"Ninety degrees north -- that is slap bang in the North Pole."},{"time":679000,"text":"I took a photo of that. Sat down on my sledge. Did a sort of video diary piece."},{"time":682000,"text":"Took a few photos. I got my satellite phone out."},{"time":684000,"text":"I warmed the battery up in my armpit."},{"time":686000,"text":"I dialed three numbers. I dialed my mum."},{"time":689000,"text":"I dialed my girlfriend. I dialed the CEO of my sponsor."},{"time":691000,"text":"And I got three voicemails."},{"time":694000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":700000,"text":"(Video): Ninety."},{"time":707000,"text":"It's a special feeling."},{"time":709000,"text":"The entire planet"},{"time":711000,"text":"is rotating"},{"time":713000,"text":"beneath my feet."},{"time":717000,"text":"The -- the whole world underneath me."},{"time":719000,"text":"I finally got through to my mum. She was at the queue of the supermarket."},{"time":722000,"text":"She started crying. She asked me to call her back."},{"time":725000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":727000,"text":"I skied on for a week past the Pole."},{"time":729000,"text":"I wanted to get as close to Canada as I could"},{"time":731000,"text":"before conditions just got too dangerous to continue."},{"time":734000,"text":"This was the last day I had on the ice."},{"time":736000,"text":"When I spoke to the -- my project management team,"},{"time":738000,"text":"they said, \"Look, Ben, conditions are getting too dangerous."},{"time":743000,"text":"There are huge areas of open water just south of your position."},{"time":745000,"text":"We'd like to pick you up."},{"time":747000,"text":"Ben, could you please look for an airstrip?\""},{"time":749000,"text":"This was the view outside my tent"},{"time":752000,"text":"when I had this fateful phone call."},{"time":756000,"text":"I'd never tried to build an airstrip before. Tony, the expedition manager, he said,"},{"time":758000,"text":"\"Look Ben, you've got to find 500 meters of"},{"time":760000,"text":"flat, thick safe ice.\""},{"time":762000,"text":"The only bit of ice I could find --"},{"time":764000,"text":"it took me 36 hours of skiing around trying to find an airstrip --"},{"time":768000,"text":"was exactly 473 meters. I could measure it with my skis."},{"time":771000,"text":"I didn't tell Tony that. I didn't tell the pilots that."},{"time":773000,"text":"I thought, it'll have to do."},{"time":776000,"text":"(Video): Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779000,"text":"It just about worked. A pretty dramatic landing --"},{"time":782000,"text":"the plane actually passed over four times,"},{"time":784000,"text":"and I was a bit worried it wasn't going to land at all."},{"time":786000,"text":"The pilot, I knew, was called Troy. I was expecting someone called Troy"},{"time":789000,"text":"that did this for a living to be a pretty tough kind of guy."},{"time":792000,"text":"I was bawling my eyes out by the time the plane landed -- a pretty emotional moment."},{"time":796000,"text":"So I thought, I've got to compose myself for Troy."},{"time":799000,"text":"I'm supposed to be the roughty toughty explorer type."},{"time":803000,"text":"The plane taxied up to where I was standing."},{"time":805000,"text":"The door opened. This guy jumped out. He's about that tall. He said, \"Hi, my name is Troy.\""},{"time":808000,"text":"(Laughter)."},{"time":810000,"text":"The co-pilot was a lady called Monica."},{"time":812000,"text":"She sat there in a sort of hand-knitted jumper."},{"time":814000,"text":"They were the least macho people I've ever met, but they made my day."},{"time":818000,"text":"Troy was smoking a cigarette on the ice;"},{"time":820000,"text":"we took a few photos. He"},{"time":822000,"text":"climbed up the ladder. He said, \"Just -- just get in the back.\""},{"time":825000,"text":"He threw his cigarette out as he got on the front,"},{"time":827000,"text":"and I climbed in the back."},{"time":829000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":830000,"text":"Taxied up and down the runway a few times,"},{"time":832000,"text":"just to flatten it out a bit, and he said, \"Right, I'm going to --"},{"time":834000,"text":"I'm going to give it a go.\" And he --"},{"time":837000,"text":"I've now learned that this is standard practice, but it had me worried at the time."},{"time":839000,"text":"He put his hand on the throttle."},{"time":841000,"text":"You can see the control for the engines is actually on the roof of the cockpit."},{"time":844000,"text":"It's that little bar there. He put his hand on the throttle."},{"time":846000,"text":"Monica very gently put her hand sort of on top of his."},{"time":848000,"text":"I thought, \"God, here we go. We're, we're -- this is all or nothing.\""},{"time":851000,"text":"Rammed it forwards. Bounced down the runway. Just took off."},{"time":853000,"text":"One of the skis just clipped a pressure ridge at the end of the runway,"},{"time":856000,"text":"banking. I could see into the cockpit, Troy battling the controls,"},{"time":859000,"text":"and he just took one hand off, reached back,"},{"time":862000,"text":"flipped a switch on the roof of the cockpit,"},{"time":864000,"text":"and it was the \"fasten seat belt\" sign you can see on the wall."},{"time":868000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":872000,"text":"And only from the air did I see the big picture."},{"time":874000,"text":"Of course, when you're on the ice, you only ever see one obstacle at a time,"},{"time":876000,"text":"whether it's a pressure ridge or there's a bit of water."},{"time":879000,"text":"This is probably why I didn't get into trouble about the length of my airstrip."},{"time":882000,"text":"I mean, it really was starting to break up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884000,"text":"Why? I'm not an explorer in the traditional sense."},{"time":887000,"text":"I'm not skiing along drawing maps;"},{"time":889000,"text":"everyone knows where the North Pole is."},{"time":891000,"text":"At the South Pole there's a big scientific base. There's an airstrip."},{"time":893000,"text":"There's a cafe and there's a tourist shop."},{"time":896000,"text":"For me, this is about exploring human limits,"},{"time":899000,"text":"about exploring the limits of physiology, of psychology"},{"time":902000,"text":"and of technology. They're the things that excite me."},{"time":905000,"text":"And it's also about potential, on a personal level."},{"time":907000,"text":"This, for me, is a chance to explore the limits --"},{"time":910000,"text":"really push the limits of my own potential, see how far they stretch."},{"time":913000,"text":"And on a wider scale, it amazes me how people go through life"},{"time":917000,"text":"just scratching the surface of their potential,"},{"time":920000,"text":"just doing three or four or five percent"},{"time":923000,"text":"of what they're truly capable of. So,"},{"time":925000,"text":"on a wider scale, I hope that this journey"},{"time":927000,"text":"was a chance to inspire other people"},{"time":929000,"text":"to think about what they want to do"},{"time":931000,"text":"with their potential, and what they want to do with the tiny amount of time"},{"time":934000,"text":"we each have on this planet."},{"time":938000,"text":"That's as close as I can come to summing that up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940000,"text":"The next question is, how do you answer the call of nature at minus 40?"},{"time":943000,"text":"The answer, of course, to which is a trade secret --"},{"time":948000,"text":"and the last question,"},{"time":950000,"text":"what's next? As quickly as possible,"},{"time":952000,"text":"if I have a minute left at the end, I'll go into more detail."},{"time":956000,"text":"What's next:"},{"time":958000,"text":"Antarctica."},{"time":960000,"text":"It's the coldest, highest,"},{"time":962000,"text":"windiest and driest continent on Earth."},{"time":966000,"text":"Late 1911, early 1912,"},{"time":968000,"text":"there was a race to be the first"},{"time":972000,"text":"to the South Pole: the heart of the Antarctic continent."},{"time":974000,"text":"If you include the coastal ice shelves, you can see that the Ross Ice Shelf --"},{"time":977000,"text":"it's the big one down here -- the Ross Ice Shelf is the size of France."},{"time":980000,"text":"Antarctica, if you include the ice shelves,"},{"time":982000,"text":"is twice the size of Australia -- it's a big place."},{"time":984000,"text":"And there's a race to get to the Pole between Amundsen,"},{"time":986000,"text":"the Norwegian -- Amundsen had dog sleds and huskies --"},{"time":989000,"text":"and Scott, the British guy, Captain Scott."},{"time":991000,"text":"Scott had sort of ponies and some tractors"},{"time":994000,"text":"and a few dogs, all of which went wrong,"},{"time":996000,"text":"and Scott and his team of four people ended up on foot."},{"time":1000000,"text":"They got to the Pole late January 1912"},{"time":1002000,"text":"to find a Norwegian flag already there."},{"time":1005000,"text":"There was a tent, a letter to the Norwegian king."},{"time":1007000,"text":"And they turned around, headed back to the coast,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"and all five of them died on the return journey."},{"time":1013000,"text":"Since then, no one has ever skied --"},{"time":1015000,"text":"this was 93 years ago -- since then, no one has ever skied"},{"time":1018000,"text":"from the coast of Antarctica to the Pole and back."},{"time":1021000,"text":"Every South Pole expedition you may have heard about"},{"time":1023000,"text":"is either flown out from the Pole or has used vehicles"},{"time":1025000,"text":"or dogs or kites to do some kind of crossing --"},{"time":1028000,"text":"no one has ever made a return journey. So that's the plan."},{"time":1030000,"text":"Two of us are doing it."},{"time":1032000,"text":"That's pretty much it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1035000,"text":"One final thought before I get to the toilet bit, is --"},{"time":1038000,"text":"is, I have a -- and I meant to scan this and I've forgotten --"},{"time":1041000,"text":"but I have a -- I have a school report. I was 13 years old,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"and it's framed above my desk at home. It says,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"\"Ben lacks sufficient impetus"},{"time":1049000,"text":"to achieve anything worthwhile.\""},{"time":1052000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1053000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1056000,"text":"I think if I've learned anything, it's this: that no one else"},{"time":1058000,"text":"is the authority on your potential."},{"time":1060000,"text":"You're the only person that decides how far you go and what you're capable of."},{"time":1063000,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, that's my story."},{"time":1067000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}